43static void
44nvkm_disp_vblank_fini(struct nvkm_event *event, int type, int head)
45{
46 struct nvkm_disp *disp = container_of(event, typeof(*disp), vblank);
47 disp->func->head.vblank_fini(disp, head);
48}
49
50static void
51nvkm_disp_vblank_init(struct nvkm_event *event, int type, int head)
52{
53 struct nvkm_disp *disp = container_of(event, typeof(*disp), vblank);
54 disp->func->head.vblank_init(disp, head);
55}
56
57static int
58nvkm_disp_vblank_ctor(struct nvkm_object *object, void *data, u32 size,
59 struct nvkm_notify *notify)
60{
61 struct nvkm_disp *disp =
62 container_of(notify->event, typeof(*disp), vblank);
63 union {
64 struct nvif_notify_head_req_v0 v0;
65 } *req = data;
66 int ret;
67
68 if (nvif_unpack(req->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
69 notify->size = sizeof(struct nvif_notify_head_rep_v0);
70 if (ret = -ENXIO, req->v0.head <= disp->vblank.index_nr) {
71 notify->types = 1;
72 notify->index = req->v0.head;
73 return 0;
74 }
75 }
76
77 return ret;
78}
79
80static const struct nvkm_event_func
81nvkm_disp_vblank_func = {
82 .ctor = nvkm_disp_vblank_ctor,
83 .init = nvkm_disp_vblank_init,
84 .fini = nvkm_disp_vblank_fini,
85};
86
87void
88nvkm_disp_vblank(struct nvkm_disp *disp, int head)
89{
90 struct nvif_notify_head_rep_v0 rep = {};
91 nvkm_event_send(&disp->vblank, 1, head, &rep, sizeof(rep));
92}
93
94static int
95nvkm_disp_hpd_ctor(struct nvkm_object *object, void *data, u32 size,
96 struct nvkm_notify *notify)
97{
98 struct nvkm_disp *disp =
99 container_of(notify->event, typeof(*disp), hpd);
100 union {
101 struct nvif_notify_conn_req_v0 v0;
102 } *req = data;
103 struct nvkm_output *outp;
104 int ret;
105
106 if (nvif_unpack(req->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
107 notify->size = sizeof(struct nvif_notify_conn_rep_v0);
108 list_for_each_entry(outp, &disp->outp, head) {
109 if (ret = -ENXIO, outp->conn->index == req->v0.conn) {
110 if (ret = -ENODEV, outp->conn->hpd.event) {
111 notify->types = req->v0.mask;
112 notify->index = req->v0.conn;
113 ret = 0;
114 }
115 break;
116 }
117 }
118 }
119
120 return ret;
121}
122
123static const struct nvkm_event_func
124nvkm_disp_hpd_func = {
125 .ctor = nvkm_disp_hpd_ctor
126};
127
128int
129nvkm_disp_ntfy(struct nvkm_object *object, u32 type, struct nvkm_event **event)
130{
131 struct nvkm_disp *disp = nvkm_disp(object->engine);
132 switch (type) {
133 case NV04_DISP_NTFY_VBLANK:
134 *event = &disp->vblank;
135 return 0;
136 case NV04_DISP_NTFY_CONN:
137 *event = &disp->hpd;
138 return 0;
139 default:
140 break;
141 }
142 return -EINVAL;
143}
144
145static void
146nvkm_disp_class_del(struct nvkm_oproxy *oproxy)
147{
148 struct nvkm_disp *disp = nvkm_disp(oproxy->base.engine);
149 mutex_lock(&disp->engine.subdev.mutex);
150 if (disp->client == oproxy)
151 disp->client = NULL;
152 mutex_unlock(&disp->engine.subdev.mutex);
153}
154
155static const struct nvkm_oproxy_func
156nvkm_disp_class = {
157 .dtor[1] = nvkm_disp_class_del,
158};
159
160static int
161nvkm_disp_class_new(struct nvkm_device *device,
162 const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass, void *data, u32 size,
163 struct nvkm_object **pobject)
164{
165 const struct nvkm_disp_oclass *sclass = oclass->engn;
166 struct nvkm_disp *disp = nvkm_disp(oclass->engine);
167 struct nvkm_oproxy *oproxy;
168 int ret;
169
170 ret = nvkm_oproxy_new_(&nvkm_disp_class, oclass, &oproxy);
171 if (ret)
172 return ret;
173 *pobject = &oproxy->base;
174
175 mutex_lock(&disp->engine.subdev.mutex);
176 if (disp->client) {
177 mutex_unlock(&disp->engine.subdev.mutex);
178 return -EBUSY;
179 }
180 disp->client = oproxy;
181 mutex_unlock(&disp->engine.subdev.mutex);
182
183 return sclass->ctor(disp, oclass, data, size, &oproxy->object);
184}
185
186static const struct nvkm_device_oclass
187nvkm_disp_sclass = {
188 .ctor = nvkm_disp_class_new,
189};
190
191static int
192nvkm_disp_class_get(struct nvkm_oclass *oclass, int index,
193 const struct nvkm_device_oclass **class)
194{
195 struct nvkm_disp *disp = nvkm_disp(oclass->engine);
196 if (index == 0) {
197 const struct nvkm_disp_oclass *root = disp->func->root(disp);
198 oclass->base = root->base;
199 oclass->engn = root;
200 *class = &nvkm_disp_sclass;
201 return 0;
202 }
203 return 1;
204}
205
206static void
207nvkm_disp_intr(struct nvkm_engine *engine)
208{
209 struct nvkm_disp *disp = nvkm_disp(engine);
210 disp->func->intr(disp);
211}
212
213static int
214nvkm_disp_fini(struct nvkm_engine *engine, bool suspend)
215{
216 struct nvkm_disp *disp = nvkm_disp(engine);
217 struct nvkm_connector *conn;
218 struct nvkm_output *outp;
219
220 list_for_each_entry(outp, &disp->outp, head) {
221 nvkm_output_fini(outp);
222 }
223
224 list_for_each_entry(conn, &disp->conn, head) {
225 nvkm_connector_fini(conn);
226 }
227
228 return 0;
229}
230
231static int
232nvkm_disp_init(struct nvkm_engine *engine)
233{
234 struct nvkm_disp *disp = nvkm_disp(engine);
235 struct nvkm_connector *conn;
236 struct nvkm_output *outp;
237
238 list_for_each_entry(conn, &disp->conn, head) {
239 nvkm_connector_init(conn);
240 }
241
242 list_for_each_entry(outp, &disp->outp, head) {
243 nvkm_output_init(outp);
244 }
245
246 return 0;
247}
248
249static void *
250nvkm_disp_dtor(struct nvkm_engine *engine)
251{
252 struct nvkm_disp *disp = nvkm_disp(engine);
253 struct nvkm_connector *conn;
254 struct nvkm_output *outp;
255 void *data = disp;
256
257 if (disp->func->dtor)
258 data = disp->func->dtor(disp);
259
260 nvkm_event_fini(&disp->vblank);
261 nvkm_event_fini(&disp->hpd);
262
263 while (!list_empty(&disp->outp)) {
264 outp = list_first_entry(&disp->outp, typeof(*outp), head);
265 list_del(&outp->head);
266 nvkm_output_del(&outp);
267 }
268
269 while (!list_empty(&disp->conn)) {
270 conn = list_first_entry(&disp->conn, typeof(*conn), head);
271 list_del(&conn->head);
272 nvkm_connector_del(&conn);
273 }
274
275 return data;
276}
277
278static const struct nvkm_engine_func
279nvkm_disp = {
280 .dtor = nvkm_disp_dtor,
281 .init = nvkm_disp_init,
282 .fini = nvkm_disp_fini,
283 .intr = nvkm_disp_intr,
284 .base.sclass = nvkm_disp_class_get,
285};
286
287int
288nvkm_disp_ctor(const struct nvkm_disp_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
289 int index, int heads, struct nvkm_disp *disp)
290{
291 struct nvkm_bios *bios = device->bios;
292 struct nvkm_output *outp, *outt, *pair;
293 struct nvkm_connector *conn;
294 struct nvbios_connE connE;
295 struct dcb_output dcbE;
296 u8 hpd = 0, ver, hdr;
297 u32 data;
298 int ret, i;
299
300 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&disp->outp);
301 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&disp->conn);
302 disp->func = func;
303 disp->head.nr = heads;
304
305 ret = nvkm_engine_ctor(&nvkm_disp, device, index, 0,
306 true, &disp->engine);
307 if (ret)
308 return ret;
309
310 /* create output objects for each display path in the vbios */
311 i = -1;
312 while ((data = dcb_outp_parse(bios, ++i, &ver, &hdr, &dcbE))) {
313 const struct nvkm_disp_func_outp *outps;
314 int (*ctor)(struct nvkm_disp *, int, struct dcb_output *,
315 struct nvkm_output **);
316
317 if (dcbE.type == DCB_OUTPUT_UNUSED)
318 continue;
319 if (dcbE.type == DCB_OUTPUT_EOL)
320 break;
321 outp = NULL;
322
323 switch (dcbE.location) {
324 case 0: outps = &disp->func->outp.internal; break;
325 case 1: outps = &disp->func->outp.external; break;
326 default:
327 nvkm_warn(&disp->engine.subdev,
328 "dcb %d locn %d unknown\n", i, dcbE.location);
329 continue;
330 }
331
332 switch (dcbE.type) {
333 case DCB_OUTPUT_ANALOG: ctor = outps->crt ; break;
334 case DCB_OUTPUT_TV : ctor = outps->tv ; break;
335 case DCB_OUTPUT_TMDS : ctor = outps->tmds; break;
336 case DCB_OUTPUT_LVDS : ctor = outps->lvds; break;
337 case DCB_OUTPUT_DP : ctor = outps->dp ; break;
338 default:
339 nvkm_warn(&disp->engine.subdev,
340 "dcb %d type %d unknown\n", i, dcbE.type);
341 continue;
342 }
343
344 if (ctor)
345 ret = ctor(disp, i, &dcbE, &outp);
346 else
347 ret = -ENODEV;
348
349 if (ret) {
350 if (ret == -ENODEV) {
351 nvkm_debug(&disp->engine.subdev,
352 "dcb %d %d/%d not supported\n",
353 i, dcbE.location, dcbE.type);
354 continue;
355 }
356 nvkm_error(&disp->engine.subdev,
357 "failed to create output %d\n", i);
358 nvkm_output_del(&outp);
359 continue;
360 }
361
362 list_add_tail(&outp->head, &disp->outp);
363 hpd = max(hpd, (u8)(dcbE.connector + 1));
364 }
365
366 /* create connector objects based on the outputs we support */
367 list_for_each_entry_safe(outp, outt, &disp->outp, head) {
368 /* bios data *should* give us the most useful information */
369 data = nvbios_connEp(bios, outp->info.connector, &ver, &hdr,
370 &connE);
371
372 /* no bios connector data... */
373 if (!data) {
374 /* heuristic: anything with the same ccb index is
375 * considered to be on the same connector, any
376 * output path without an associated ccb entry will
377 * be put on its own connector
378 */
379 int ccb_index = outp->info.i2c_index;
380 if (ccb_index != 0xf) {
381 list_for_each_entry(pair, &disp->outp, head) {
382 if (pair->info.i2c_index == ccb_index) {
383 outp->conn = pair->conn;
384 break;
385 }
386 }
387 }
388
389 /* connector shared with another output path */
390 if (outp->conn)
391 continue;
392
393 memset(&connE, 0x00, sizeof(connE));
394 connE.type = DCB_CONNECTOR_NONE;
395 i = -1;
396 } else {
397 i = outp->info.connector;
398 }
399
400 /* check that we haven't already created this connector */
401 list_for_each_entry(conn, &disp->conn, head) {
402 if (conn->index == outp->info.connector) {
403 outp->conn = conn;
404 break;
405 }
406 }
407
408 if (outp->conn)
409 continue;
410
411 /* apparently we need to create a new one! */
412 ret = nvkm_connector_new(disp, i, &connE, &outp->conn);
413 if (ret) {
414 nvkm_error(&disp->engine.subdev,
415 "failed to create output %d conn: %d\n",
416 outp->index, ret);
417 nvkm_connector_del(&outp->conn);
418 list_del(&outp->head);
419 nvkm_output_del(&outp);
420 continue;
421 }
422
423 list_add_tail(&outp->conn->head, &disp->conn);
424 }
425
426 ret = nvkm_event_init(&nvkm_disp_hpd_func, 3, hpd, &disp->hpd);
427 if (ret)
428 return ret;
429
430 ret = nvkm_event_init(&nvkm_disp_vblank_func, 1, heads, &disp->vblank);
431 if (ret)
432 return ret;
433
434 return 0;
435}
436
437int
438nvkm_disp_new_(const struct nvkm_disp_func *func, struct nvkm_device *device,
439 int index, int heads, struct nvkm_disp **pdisp)
440{
441 if (!(*pdisp = kzalloc(sizeof(**pdisp), GFP_KERNEL)))
442 return -ENOMEM;
443 return nvkm_disp_ctor(func, device, index, heads, *pdisp);
444}
